title: Neo-Nazi rally London video | Man sees friend: ‘What are you doing here’? |
text:
A video posted to YouTube appears to show the moment an English man spots his friend taking part in a Neo-Nazi rally.
The far-right anti-immigration rally in Wigan took place on September 19 and shows a man reacting with surprise that his friend is taking part.
“What the f*** are you doing there? What are you doing there?” the man shouts.
The march was organised by the Neo-Nazi National Front and the North West Infidels and was met by counter-protesters from Hope Not Hate and the Liverpool Anti-Fascists, according to reports.
The woman who posted the video Ellen Thootly wrote she has been taking part in the counter protest to the “National Front/Nazis protesting against refugees“ and as she was filming from the counter protest side she managed to capture this “heartbreaking” moment.
Man sees friend on the other side of a protest
 Man spots friend at Neo-Nazi rally
